post.text:
VIDEO | Here's what Maharashtra Deputy CM Ajit Pawar (
@AjitPawarSpeaks
) said on the language row:

"Nothing will happen to someone who says that we are living in Maharashtra but can't speak very good Marathi. However, we respect the language and will try to learn it. It doesn't happen always, people react badly many times. You should respect the language of the state you live in, at least a little bit."

(Full video available on PTI Videos - 
ptivideos.com)

